HW10: Data Visualization I

Alissa Seal

24 July 2020

Install and load libraries

library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(GGally)
library(patchwork)

Import Sparrows Data

sparrows_raw <- read_tsv(here("data", "sparrows.txt"))
Parsed with column specification:
cols(
  wingcrd = col_double(),
  flatwing = col_double(),
  tarsus = col_double(),
  head = col_double(),
  culmen = col_double(),
  nalospi = col_double(),
  wt = col_double(),
  bandstat = col_double(),
  initials = col_double(),
  Year = col_double(),
  Month = col_double(),
  Day = col_double(),
  Location = col_double(),
  SpeciesCode = col_double(),
  Sex = col_double(),
  Age = col_double()
)

Check

sparrows_raw

Wrangle Sparrow Data

sparrows <- sparrows_raw %>% 
  mutate(box_group = "Sparrows",
         row_order = 1:nrow(.))

Check

view(sparrows)

Figure 2: Outliers

Run Code

plot_box<- sparrows %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = box_group, y = wingcrd)) +
  geom_boxplot(width = 0.25) +
  labs(x = NULL, y = "Wing length (mm)")

Run Cleveland dot plot

plot_cleveland <- sparrows %>%
  ggplot(aes(x= wingcrd,y=row_order))+
  geom_point()+
  labs(x="Wing length (mm)", y="Order of the date")

Display plots

plot_box+plot_cleveland

Add coord_flip()

plot_box+plot_cleveland+coord_flip()

Figure 3: Outliers

culmen plot

p_culmen <- sparrows %>% 
  ggplot(aes(y = row_order)) +
  geom_point(aes(x = culmen)) +
  theme(axis.title.y=element_blank(),
        axis.text.y=element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y=element_blank())
